I have a process that current just pulls a program every minute and gets the last 5m of data.. After about a week of it constantly running I run into issues where the socket never returns any data.. I thought about using the timeout parameter but that doesnt do anything with the WebSocketTransport..

Here is my code to read the data
```
def get_program_data(self, program: str, start: datetime, stop: datetime) -> (dict, dict):
        data = {}
        metadata = {}
        with SignalFlowClient(self.__app_key, compress=True) as client:
            result = client.execute(program=program, start=self.to_epoch_ms(start),
                                    stop=self.to_epoch_ms(stop),
                                    resolution=self.__resolution, immediate=True,
                                    max_delay=10)
            for msg in result.stream():
                if isinstance(msg, messages.DataMessage):
                    if msg.logical_timestamp_ms in data:
                        data[msg.logical_timestamp_ms].update(msg.data)
                    else:
                        data[msg.logical_timestamp_ms] = msg.data
                elif isinstance(msg, messages.MetadataMessage):
                    metadata[msg.tsid] = msg.properties

        return data, metadata
```

The strange thing is it runs fine for a couple days and then just hangs.. 

The range is pretty short as well... 
`now - timedelta(minutes=5), now`

Any tips/advice would be super helpful.. Im not sure what exactly could be going on as no errors have bubbled up..
